In many cases, fibers are not straight between crosslinks. The stiffness of networks with crimped fibers is much smaller than that of networks of same architecture, but with straight fibers - see Figure 5. The two parameters of the map are the amplitude of crimp (fibers have sinusoidal shape of amplitude cL, where L is the distance between the end nodes) and the fraction of the fibers of the network which are crimped, f.

