Warning: The results shown above refer to networks which are not embedded in a solid or viscoelastic fluid. The presence of a matrix alters significantly the failure mode.  Likewise, molecular networks in which nonbonded interactions between molecules are important, rupture in ways different from what is presented here. This is because the nonbonded interactions convey a mechanics somewhat similar to that of a network embedded in matrix.

